<br>
I think all this bickering over what game will and will not be better gets alittle out of hand sometimes and everyone has thier right to have opinions, people play games that they like and enjoy, as long as the player of the game is happy, what else really matters?<br>
<br>
I dont really understand why people think graphics make the game, the content of the game is far more important then the graphics, from all the FAQS ive read and what ive seen E3 moviewise on WoW, the conent and character development far surpasses EQ.<br>
<br>
In EQ you go one way and one way only... Levels + Gear, skills are irrelivant, the WoW FAQS ive read have stated that people can have a choice of how they take the character and advance them, while they still have levels to be achieved for higher end content, they also have other avenues to play, take for example the quest system, you will beable to see a list of things you could recieve upon completion of the quest, and people wont be left out for only having 1 item drop or be awarded at the end of the quest, multiple people can get that item or reward, and encourages groups to work together moreso then in EQ.<br>
<br>
Also some of the quests and gameplay will make people accually take part in the 10% of the PvP part of the game, and rewards for the PvP are unique aswell so people will know that the person took part in, and won a pvp battle (gladiator style arena WHERE people/players view from the stands and can place BETS on people/players/monsters, or where people can go in a gauntlet of challenges while people in the crowd get money for seeing heros or villians spill blood how cool is that? and its level restricted too) now tell me that is not a great thing to have in a game.<br>
<br>
WoW's 'cartoony' graphics may not appeal to everyone, but sooner or later WoW will make a big impact, not because of the (according to some) subpar graphics, but the content in the game will be more fun then people are thinking<br>
<br>
oh and another thing.. anyone think its ODD that EQ2's demo at E3 had buggy models with missing limbs and heads while the person running the booth said 'heh dont worry about that it will get fixed later', and WoW run without a hint of lag or framerate delay on a laptop and various CPU's in the blizzard booth? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pestilnse>Pestilnse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/18/03 1:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> here is a link on what was shown so far in terms of PvP in WoW....<br>
